results.description: My dog Eucle and I were on a morning hike up a canyon called Molybdenite Creek Canyon near Bridgeport CA.  I took this photo looking back down trail as we headed to our vehicle.  We were walking thru those aspen down below when I saw something light brown come down off the sidehill on the left, walking thru the aspens, and then onto the trail. It was a bear, a beautiful almost blond and cinnamon blackbear. It took one look at us then turned off the trail and ran at full speed down into the bushes. I started talking loudly to my dog and we got out of there also !
